headline: Tariffs Are Weighing Down the Transportation Industry, but This Dividend-Paying Value Stock Is Built to Last
summary: The industry can be a good barometer for economic growth.  Union Pacific (NYSE: UNP) is one of the largest railroads in North America -- dominating railroad shipping lines west of the Mississippi River.  Union Pacific could be vulnerable to tariffs between the U.S. and its North American neighbors, but that doesn't mean that tariffs would derail its investment thesis.
